review_blob: Rich, smooth and very satisfying.  First tried this at Anacortes Oktoberfest - want more of this beer
This English IPA is really nice.  I am not a fan of West Coast IPAs.  The blend of Rye and use of English malts and hops makes this really nice and one I can really enjoy.
Was thrilled to see this beer at Grinders (Shoreline, WA) - paired wonderfully with their Meatball/Sausage Sandwich.  Wonderful rich malty tones, but not heavy.
Very nice American Pale Ale.  Smooth and refreshing.  Very quaff-able. I always enjoy this beer and one I look forward to.
Better than I remember this beer from my last time.  I aged this bottle for a year, might be why its improved.
This is an amazing beer.  Very much a sipper, on the sweet side, but very nice.  Hard to get, had to go to Canada for this one.
Very nice an enjoyable beer, especially in the warm Maui weather. Best had on the island of Maui.

This is almost perfection, or maybe it is.  Some intrigued reading the history of this almost extinct beer style "Burton Ale".  I have never tasted anything like this and really want to have more.  I heard that Foggy Noggin is planning on bottling this beer, and I will be stocking up on this when it happens.  This may be the best beer I have ever had.

Not normally a beer I would choose, but thanks to a good friend I was able to try this.  This beer is sold out, but hope they brew it again.  Complex and very approachable at the same time. Like nothing I have ever tasted before. I like it, alot!

This is a big and bold beer, but surprisingly quaffable.  This is a very special treat, but very hard to find.  Tastes like something I have had in Ireland.  Really an amazing beer and worth seeking out.

This is an amazing beer.  I was able to control myself and not consume all of my 2011 stash and compare a bottle of last years with the 2012 edition.  First, the 2012 is even better than I remember the 2011 tasting when it was fresh.  Wonderful aroma or malty tones, great full-bodied falvor with a warming sensation that lingers long with a fantastic dry finish.  The 2011 has aged beautifully and think the 2012 version will age even better.  Well done!

This is not what I expected, but really enjoyed it.  Rich and full of malty flavors that go on forever, but finish to a slightly dry finish.  There are flavors I dont think I have ever tasted. So good I think I am ready to dance!

One best examples I have ever had of this beer style. Had it in the brewerys tasting room and learned that it is lagered for 3 months.  I can see the crispness from this long laggering.  Nice malty tones and pretty well hopped with German hops.  Really nice beer, they only brew this once a year.  I had better go back and get another growler.

The more I try this beer, the more I like it.  It has a moderate body to it, but is full flavored and finishes nice and roasty with a dry feeling.  More roasty that a typical Porter, which is probably why I like this.  More flavorful as it warms up.

I have had this beer at the James Gate Brewery, as well as all over America.  They do a great job of making sure this beer tastes pretty much the same everywhere.  Liquid Goodness! Rich, smooth, delicate and bold at the same time.  Nice toasty, roastiness and just the right amount of bitterness at the end.  I can drink this pint after pint.  Love it!

I was really surprised how good this beer was when I first tasted it.  Really nice malty - toasty flavors upfront that transform into a smooth (honey-like) mid flavor.  Finish is dry and lingers with a nice hop image.  Too bad this is not on more often.
This has been one of my favorite beers for a long time.  Great malty flavors and hopped just the right amount to make this beer scream for another taste.
beer_name: Maritime Pacific Flagship Red Alt Ale

review_blob: Not sure I have ever had am English Pale before.  I really like the forward hoppiness - flavor, taste and aroma.  Finish is so smooth, but not that bitter.  This is really good.  I need to get another growler of this one.
Might be the best ESB in the world.  Just a treat from the start.  Malty, smooth, balance and perfectly crafted. The finish is unique and lingers calling for another pint.
Really nice interpretation of the German Alt style.  Crisp and clean with a great flvor profile.  Please start distributing this into the Seattle market.
I always order a pint of this when I see it on tap.  Great small beer, with complex flavors of malt, wood and great finish.  Wish I could find this more often.

This is such q wonderful completely satisfying beer.  Has to be one of the finest crafted beers in the world.  Rich and malty, but has just enough alcohol to transform this into a very pleasing dry finish that lingers on.  WOW!
UPDATED: JUL 17, 2012

Hard to find this style done very well and very well is what this one is.  Been going to the Foggy Noggin tasting room for quite some time and just love this beer.  I am a bog fan of session beers and this is my go to beer.  Nice matly tones of bicuity, bready and finishes with a pleasant dry bitterness.
